"""
SETUP

1. Install Python (if not already installed).
2. Open the project in PyCharm.
3. Create and activate a virtual environment (.venv).
4. Create a requirements.txt file and install all required project dependencies.
5. Export your bank transaction history as a CSV file.
6. Save the exported CSV file to a location on your computer.
7. Run the application.
8. When prompted, select your bank CSV file using the file selection dialog.
9. The application will validate the selected file and verify the required transaction data.
10. After successful validation, the application will:
      - Determine the reporting period.
      - Calculate your financial summary.
      - Generate monthly financial charts.
11. Choose whether you would like to save the generated charts as image files.
